<l>vēṟṟumai yalvaḻi yeṇṇe ṉuṇavuppeyar</l>
<l>vēṟṟumai yiyaṟkai nilaiyalu murittē</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>The noun <foreign xml:lang="ta">eṇ</foreign> denoting food is sometimes of the same nature</l>
<l>in non-case-relation as in case-relation <foreign xml:lang="ta">sandhi.</foreign><note place="foot">i.e. the noun <foreign xml:lang="ta">eṇ</foreign> ' sesame seed ' may have its <foreign xml:lang="ta">-ṇ</foreign> assimilated to <foreign xml:lang="ta">-ṭ</foreign> before a following plosive, e.g. <foreign xml:lang="ta">eṇ + ciṟitu &gt; eṭciṟitu.</foreign></note></l>
      </lg>
